    "plan_content": "Here's the full implementation plan:\n\n---\n\n## Plan: Stepper Compound Component\n\n**2 new files, 2 registry entries â€” no existing component files modified.**\n\n---\n\n### Architecture\n\nThe Stepper uses **two React contexts** (like `carousel.tsx` uses its own context) â€” no Radix UI needed since no Radix stepper primitive exists:\n\n- **`StepperContext`** â†’ root provides `{ activeStep, orientation }` to all descendants\n- **`StepperItemContext`** â†’ each `StepperItem` provides `{ step, state }`, where `state` is derived by comparing `step` to `activeStep` (`\"completed\" | \"active\" | \"pending\"`)\n\nBoth have enforcing custom hooks that throw if used outside their provider.\n\n---\n\n### `ui/stepper.tsx` â€” 7 named exports\n\n| Component | Element | Key detail |\n|---|---|---|\n| `Stepper` | `<div>` | Provides context; `flex-row items-center` (H) or `flex-col` (V); adds `group/stepper` class for descendant selectors |\n| `StepperItem` | `<div>` | Reads root context, derives state, provides item context; **`flex-1`** in horizontal so items share equal width |\n| `StepperTrigger` | `<button>` | Reads item context; renders step number by default (`children ?? step`); styled via `data-[state=completed/active/pending]` â€” completed=filled primary, active=primary border, pending=muted |\n| `StepperTitle` | `<p>` | `text-sm font-medium` |\n| `StepperDescription` | `<p>` | `text-xs text-muted-foreground` |\n| `StepperSeparator` | `<div>` | Reads both contexts; `h-px flex-1` (H) or `h-6 w-px ms-[15px]` (V, centered under trigger); `bg-primary` when `state === \"completed\"`, `bg-border` otherwise |\n| `StepperContent` | `<div>` | Returns `null` when `step !== activeStep` |\n\n---\n\n### `examples/stepper-demo.tsx`\n\n3-step horizontal stepper (Account â†’ Profile â†’ Complete) with:\n- `React.useState(1)` for `activeStep`\n- `StepperTrigger` + `StepperTitle` + `StepperSeparator` per item (separator omitted on step 3)\n- `StepperContent` panels per step\n- \"Previous\" / \"Next\" `Button` components with boundary `disabled` states\n\n---\n\n### Registry entries\n\n**`ui/_registry.ts`** â€” insert between existing `\"spinner\"` and `\"switch\"`:\n```ts\n{ name: \"stepper\", type: \"registry:ui\", files: [{ path: \"ui/stepper.tsx\", type: \"registry:ui\" }] }\n```\n\n**`examples/_registry.ts`** â€” append before closing `]`:\n```ts\n{ name: \"stepper-demo\", type: \"registry:example\", registryDependencies: [\"stepper\", \"button\"], files: [{ path: \"examples/stepper-demo.tsx\", type: \"registry:example\" }] }\n```",
